No specific information on the average high temperatures for the designated parks was found, but here are the average temperatures for the parks I could find:

Glacier National Park (U.S.): The average temperature in Glacier National Park varies throughout the year, with the warmest month being July, when the average high temperature reaches 70°F (21°C).

Yosemite National Park: The average temperature in Yosemite National Park also varies, with July and August being the warmest months, reaching highs of 87°F (30°C).

Zion National Park: The average high temperature in Zion National Park ranges from 90-105°F (32-41°C) in the summer months.

Grand Canyon National Park: The average high temperature in Grand Canyon National Park is around 85°F (29°C) in the summer.

Rocky Mountain National Park: In Rocky Mountain National Park, the average high temperature in the summer months can reach 84°F (29°C).

Yellowstone National Park: Yellowstone National Park sees an average high temperature of 76°F (24°C) in the summer.

Olympic National Park: The average high temperature in Olympic National Park is around 68°F (20°C) in July and August.

Please note that these are general averages and the temperatures can vary depending on the specific location within the parks and the time of year.
